# ============================================================================
# devstack.list  --  Corvid OS arm64 / Pi 5  coding-friendly DEV STACK
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Plain package list for the Pi build (provisioning/build-pi5.sh feeds it to
# `apt install` on the arm64 rootfs). One package per line; '#' comments live
# on their own line, never trailing a package.
#
# This is the ARM analog of the amd64 config/package-lists/devstack.list.chroot.
# Every package here is arch-independent in Ubuntu noble: the same toolchains,
# language runtimes, and CLI utilities ship for arm64. So the list ports 1:1.
#
# NOT installed here (handled by hooks / runtime, because they are not plain
# base-repo packages):
#   * Rust toolchain  -> rustup (system-wide under /opt), via the devstack hook.
#   * VS Code ('code') -> Microsoft's apt repo. Microsoft ships an arm64 `code`
#     .deb, so the same hook works on the Pi; it just points at the arm64 build.
#   * Docker Engine from Docker's own repo is optional; `docker.io` below is the
#     Ubuntu-packaged Docker and is arm64-native, so the base image is
#     self-contained without adding Docker's external repo.
# ============================================================================

# --- Toolchain / build essentials -------------------------------------------
build-essential
gcc
g++
clang
clangd
lld
llvm
make
cmake
ninja-build
pkg-config
autoconf
automake
libtool
gdb
lldb
valgrind
ccache

# --- Version control ---------------------------------------------------------
git
git-lfs
git-gui
gitk
tig

# --- Python ------------------------------------------------------------------
python3
python3-dev
python3-pip
python3-venv
python3-wheel
python3-setuptools
pipx

# --- Go ----------------------------------------------------------------------
golang-go

# --- Node.js / npm -----------------------------------------------------------
# noble ships Node 18.x for arm64. If a newer LTS is required, NodeSource has an
# arm64 channel that can be added at the archive layer; the base package keeps
# the image self-contained.
nodejs
npm

# --- Ruby --------------------------------------------------------------------
ruby-full

# --- Editors -----------------------------------------------------------------
neovim
vim
# (VS Code 'code' comes from the devstack hook's Microsoft apt repo -- arm64
# build -- not from this list.)

# --- Containers / dev sandboxes ---------------------------------------------
docker.io
docker-compose-v2
docker-buildx
podman
buildah
skopeo
distrobox
# uidmap provides newuidmap/newgidmap, required for rootless podman/distrobox
uidmap
fuse-overlayfs
slirp4netns

# --- Shell + terminal quality of life ---------------------------------------
zsh
zsh-autosuggestions
zsh-syntax-highlighting
tmux
bash-completion

# --- CLI utilities the dev stack + later hooks rely on ----------------------
jq
yq
curl
wget
ca-certificates
gnupg
# apt-transport-https is used by the VS Code https repo added in the hook
apt-transport-https
software-properties-common
unzip
zip
xz-utils
tree
htop
ripgrep
fd-find
fzf
bat
direnv
shellcheck
